**Summary:** In `cynewulf-andreas-07b573`, chapter 1, Andrew is first led to prison in paragraph `p-5d78fc`. The sequence: the devil betrays Andrew to the Mermedonians (`p-cdd18f`), his hands are bound and he is dragged through the stone-paved streets all day (`p-34b202`), and at evening "the people then led their loathed enemy to the prison" (`p-5d78fc`). The poem then has him led out twice more for successive days of scourging, each time returned to the prison at nightfall.
